Introduction

Hong Da Bin, formerly known by his stage name DPR Live, is a South Korean rapper and singer under Dream Perfect Regime and CTYL. DPR stands for "Dream Perfect Regime". He released his debut EP, "Coming to You Live", on March 15, 2017. He then released his second EP, "Her", on December 7, 2017. His first studio album, "Is Anybody Out There?" was released on March 3, 2020.

In 2023, he announced that he would be promoting under his birth name moving forward and established a new label CTYL.
